description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Newly Qualified Mental Health Practitioner &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Up to £27,000 per annum &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent: Full Time, 40 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Wing College, Bournemouth &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cambian Group, the UK’s largest provider of specialist services in children’s residential care, education, mental health rehabilitation and learning disabilities, is looking for a dedicated individual to join the company as a Mental Health Practitioner. This post is a newly created role to join a successful expanding therapy team at Wing College in Bournemouth, the post will require someone who is motivated to work with young people and help them reach their personal best.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cambian Wing College&lt;/strong&gt; is a specialist further education college placements for young people aged 16-25 with a diagnosis of Asperger’s Syndrome or high-functioning autism, offering day placements and 38 to 52 week residential placements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining an established onsite clinical team of professionals that include, Mental Health Nurse, OTs, SaLTs, Psychology and Psychiatry all providing a therapeutic service to young people placed at the College. You will be working alongside the existing mental health practitioner assessing and identifying the student’s mental and emotional health needs taking a “hands-on” approach. It is essential that you will be a strong team player, with excellent communication, organisational and time management skills. Following the initial assessments you will undertake either direct and/or indirect work including with students, holding a skills lead case load, delivering tailored groups with student’s and members of the MDT, offering reactive and proactive ad-hoc support, alongside consultation and training to both educational and residential care staff. The role will require autonomous practice and an individual who is able to think ‘outside the box’.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidate Profile&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated, forward thinking Mental Health Practitioner to join our friendly team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Person Specification &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hold a professional and accredited registration with relevant professional body&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be a strong team player, with excellent communication skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good organisational and time management skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;New qualified candidates welcome to apply&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beneficial&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience in working with children &amp; adolescents&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of supporting young people with ASD and High functioning autism&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Providing consultation to groups&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full support from a multidisciplinary team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical supervision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Developmental opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Research opportunities &amp; support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Internal/external training on new initiatives&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Preceptorship for NQs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also learn from some of the most dedicated and inspirational people in our profession.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will need to meet the person specification in order to be offered this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cambian is committed to Safeguarding and protecting the young people and service users within our care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All candidates will be subject to an enhanced DBS check and reference checks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cambian is an equal opportunities employer.&lt;/p&gt;
